abstract: PARIS, Nov. 6.--The Gaulois publishes a report of an interview with the Marquis Tseng, the Chinese Ambassador, at his residence in Folkestone, England. The Marquis said if war occurred between France and China, which he believed to be probable, the Kingdom of Annam would become the ally of China. The French, he said, would require 40,000 troops to overcome their united forces. Meantime, England's commercial interests would compel her to intervene.
